   "source": [
    "# Day 2 — Deep Learning & Transformer Architecture\n",
    "\n",
    "In this module, we transition from classical machine learning to PyTorch, building neural networks from scratch. We cover basic tensor operations, training feedforward neural networks, and inspecting BERT's attention weights.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Objectives\n",
    "- Build and train a feedforward neural network in PyTorch using the Iris dataset.\n",
    "- Inspect attention maps of a pre-trained BERT model.\n",
    "- **Extended Implementation:** Build a custom Swish activation function and compare it with ReLU, write an Early Stopping callback class, and visualize self-attention matrices with heatmaps."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install dependencies\n",
    "!pip install torch torchvision transformers matplotlib seaborn -q\n",
    "print(\"✅ Libraries installed.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## PyTorch Tensors\n",
    "Tensors are the fundamental data structures in PyTorch, representing multi-dimensional grids of numbers that can run on CPUs or GPUs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import torch\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a tensor\n",
    "t = torch.tensor([[1.0, 2.0], [3.0, 4.0]])\n",
    "print(\"Tensor:\\n\", t)\n",
    "print(\"Shape:\", t.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Device:\", t.device)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Is GPU available?\n",
    "device = \"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\"\n",
    "print(\"Active Device:\", device)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Training a Neural Network (Iris Classification)\n",
    "We construct a simple fully connected neural network in PyTorch to classify Iris flower types."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import torch.nn as nn\n",
    "import torch.optim as optim\n",
    "from sklearn.datasets import load_iris\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "\n",
    "# Data Prep\n",
    "iris = load_iris()\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X = scaler.fit_transform(iris.data)\n",
    "y = iris.target\n",
    "\n",
    "X_tensor = torch.tensor(X, dtype=torch.float32)\n",
    "y_tensor = torch.tensor(y, dtype=torch.long)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Neural Network definition\n",
    "class IrisNet(nn.Module):\n",
    "    def __init__(self):\n",
    "        super(IrisNet, self).__init__()\n",
    "        self.fc1 = nn.Linear(4, 16)\n",
    "        self.relu = nn.ReLU()\n",
    "        self.fc2 = nn.Linear(16, 3)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def forward(self, x):\n",
    "        x = self.fc1(x)\n",
    "        x = self.relu(x)\n",
    "        x = self.fc2(x)\n",
    "        return x\n",
    "\n",
    "model = IrisNet()\n",
    "criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n",
    "optimizer = optim.SGD(model.parameters(), lr=0.1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Training Loop\n",
    "for epoch in range(100):\n",
    "    optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
    "    outputs = model(X_tensor)\n",
    "    loss = criterion(outputs, y_tensor)\n",
    "    loss.backward()\n",
    "    optimizer.step()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if (epoch+1) % 20 == 0:\n",
    "        print(f"Epoch {epoch+1}/100, Loss: {loss.item():.4f}")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## BERT Self-Attention Weights Inspection\n",
    "We load a pre-trained BERT model to inspect the dimensions and layout of the attention weight layers."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from transformers import BertModel, BertTokenizer\n",
    "\n",
    "tokenizer = BertTokenizer.from_pretrained('bert-base-uncased')\n",
    "bert_model = BertModel.from_pretrained('bert-base-uncased', output_attentions=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "inputs = tokenizer(\"Learning about self attention mechanics.\", return_tensors=\"pt\")\n",
    "outputs = bert_model(**inputs)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Attentions is a tuple of length 12 (number of layers)\n",
    "# Each layer has shape: [batch_size, num_heads, sequence_length, sequence_length]\n",
    "attentions = outputs.attentions\n",
    "print(\"Number of layers:\", len(attentions))\n",
    "print(\"Attention map shape in layer 1:\", attentions[0].shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "# Extended Implementation\n",
    "Below are implementation techniques covering custom activation functions, early stopping logic, and attention heatmap visualisations.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1. Custom Activation Function (Swish / SiLU)\n",
    "We implement the Swish activation function from scratch and compare convergence rates against standard ReLU."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class CustomSwish(nn.Module):\n",
    "    def __init__(self):\n",
    "        super(CustomSwish, self).__init__()\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def forward(self, x):\n",
    "        return x * torch.sigmoid(x)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Constructing two networks to compare\n",
    "class NetWithReLU(nn.Module):\n",
    "    def __init__(self):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "        self.net = nn.Sequential(nn.Linear(4, 32), nn.ReLU(), nn.Linear(32, 3))\n",
    "    def forward(self, x): return self.net(x)\n",
    "\n",
    "class NetWithSwish(nn.Module):\n",
    "    def __init__(self):        super().__init__()\n",
    "        self.net = nn.Sequential(nn.Linear(4, 32), CustomSwish(), nn.Linear(32, 3))\n",
    "    def forward(self, x): return self.net(x)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Training both and recording losses\n",
    "def train_model(net, X_data, y_data, epochs=150):\n",
    "    optimizer = optim.Adam(net.parameters(), lr=0.01)\n",
    "    criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n",
    "    losses = []\n",
    "    for epoch in range(epochs):\n",
    "        optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
    "        out = net(X_data)\n",
    "        loss = criterion(out, y_data)\n",
    "        loss.backward()\n",
    "        optimizer.step()\n",
    "        losses.append(loss.item())\n",
    "    return losses\n",
    "\n",
    "losses_relu = train_model(NetWithReLU(), X_tensor, y_tensor)\n",
    "losses_swish = train_model(NetWithSwish(), X_tensor, y_tensor)\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))\n",
    "plt.plot(losses_relu, label='ReLU Loss')\n",
    "plt.plot(losses_swish, label='Swish (Custom) Loss', linestyle='--')\n",
    "plt.title('Convergence comparison: ReLU vs Swish Activation')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Epoch')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Loss')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(True)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2. Early Stopping Callback\n",
    "We define an early stopping controller class that terminates training when validation loss fails to decrease further after a specified patience threshold."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class EarlyStopping:\n",
    "    def __init__(self, patience=5, min_delta=0.0):\n",
    "        self.patience = patience\n",
    "        self.min_delta = min_delta\n",
    "        self.counter = 0\n",
    "        self.best_loss = None\n",
    "        self.early_stop = False\n",
    "\n",
    "    def __call__(self, val_loss):\n",
    "        if self.best_loss is None:\n",
    "            self.best_loss = val_loss\n",
    "        elif val_loss > self.best_loss - self.min_delta:\n",
    "            self.counter += 1\n",
    "            if self.counter >= self.patience:\n",
    "                self.early_stop = True\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            self.best_loss = val_loss\n",
    "            self.counter = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mock training demonstration\n",
    "model_es = NetWithReLU()\n",
    "optimizer = optim.Adam(model_es.parameters(), lr=0.05)\n",
    "criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n",
    "early_stopping = EarlyStopping(patience=10, min_delta=0.001)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Starting training with Early Stopping...\")\n",
    "for epoch in range(200):\n",
    "    model_es.train()\n",
    "    optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
    "    out = model_es(X_tensor)\n",
    "    loss = criterion(out, y_tensor)\n",
    "    loss.backward()\n",
    "    optimizer.step()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Check stopping condition\n",
    "    early_stopping(loss.item())\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if (epoch + 1) % 10 == 0 or early_stopping.early_stop:\n",
    "        print(f\"Epoch {epoch+1:03d} | Loss: {loss.item():.5f} | Best Loss: {early_stopping.best_loss:.5f} | Counter: {early_stopping.counter}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if early_stopping.early_stop:\n",
    "        print(f\"🛑 Early stopping triggered at epoch {epoch+1}!\")\n",
    "        break"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3. Self-Attention Visualizer\n",
    "We display a heatmap representation of self-attention weights extracted from the BERT model, mapping dependency strengths between input tokens."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Tokenize sentence and extract tokens\n",
    "sentence = \"Learning about self attention mechanics.\"\n",
    "inputs = tokenizer(sentence, return_tensors=\"pt\")\n",
    "tokens = tokenizer.convert_ids_to_tokens(inputs['input_ids'][0])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extract attention weights for the 1st layer, 1st attention head\n",
    "attention_matrix = attentions[0][0, 0].detach().numpy()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(7, 6))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(attention_matrix, xticklabels=tokens, yticklabels=tokens, annot=True, cmap='viridis', fmt='.2f')\n",
    "plt.title('BERT Layer 1, Head 1 Attention Heatmap')\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
    "plt.yticks(rotation=0)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
